title: John Stockwell: CIA Whistle Blower
description:
For more related content, please visit: https://archive.org/details/@altviewstv-fanclub

This can be found on other channels, but generally in two parts. This is both parts combined.

John Stockwell is the highest ranking CIA whistle blower to date.

Author of "Search for Enemies" 1987 college lecture recording.
John R. Stockwell is a former CIA officer for thirteen years serving seven tours of duty. After managing U.S. involvement in the Angolan Civil War as Chief of the Angola Task Force during its 1975 covert operations, he resigned and wrote In Search of Enemies, a book which remains the only detailed, insider's account of a major CIA "covert action."
